HEADWORD: Pignerate
<hw>Pig"ner*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pigneratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>pignerate</ets> to pledge.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To pledge or pawn.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to receive in pawn, as a pawnbroker does.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pignoration</ent>⟦br⟧
